{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I work with a species called \"Bonobo.\""},{"time":3000,"text":"And I'm happy most of the time,"},{"time":5000,"text":"because I think this is the happiest species on the planet."},{"time":8000,"text":"It's kind of a well-kept secret."},{"time":11000,"text":"This species lives only in the Congo."},{"time":13000,"text":"And they're not in too many zoos, because of their sexual behavior."},{"time":19000,"text":"Their sexual behavior is too human-like"},{"time":21000,"text":"for most of us to be comfortable with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":24000,"text":"But --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":25000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":26000,"text":"actually, we have a lot to learn from them, because they're a very"},{"time":31000,"text":"egalitarian society and they're a very empathetic society."},{"time":35000,"text":"And sexual behavior is not confined to one aspect of their life"},{"time":39000,"text":"that they sort of set aside."},{"time":42000,"text":"It permeates their entire life."},{"time":44000,"text":"And it's used for communication."},{"time":47000,"text":"And it's used for conflict resolution."},{"time":49000,"text":"And I think perhaps somewhere in our history we sort of,"},{"time":53000,"text":"divided our lives up into lots of parts."},{"time":56000,"text":"We divided our world up with lots of categories."},{"time":60000,"text":"And so everything sort of has a place that it has to fit."},{"time":63000,"text":"But I don't think that we were that way initially."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"There are many people who think that the animal world is hard-wired"},{"time":71000,"text":"and that there's something very, very special about man."},{"time":75000,"text":"Maybe it's his ability to have causal thought."},{"time":79000,"text":"Maybe it's something special in his brain"},{"time":82000,"text":"that allows him to have language."},{"time":84000,"text":"Maybe it's something special in his brain"},{"time":87000,"text":"that allows him to make tools or to have mathematics."},{"time":92000,"text":"Well, I don't know. There were Tasmanians who were discovered"},{"time":98000,"text":"around the 1600s and they had no fire."},{"time":102000,"text":"They had no stone tools."},{"time":105000,"text":"To our knowledge they had no music."},{"time":109000,"text":"So when you compare them to the Bonobo,"},{"time":114000,"text":"the Bonobo is a little hairier."},{"time":116000,"text":"He doesn't stand quite as upright."},{"time":121000,"text":"But there are a lot of similarities."},{"time":124000,"text":"And I think that as we look at culture,"},{"time":128000,"text":"we kind of come to understand"},{"time":131000,"text":"how we got to where we are."},{"time":133000,"text":"And I don't really think it's in our biology;"},{"time":136000,"text":"I think we've attributed it to our biology,"},{"time":138000,"text":"but I don't really think it's there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"So what I want to do now is introduce you"},{"time":143000,"text":"to a species called the Bonobo."},{"time":147000,"text":"This is Kanzi."},{"time":149000,"text":"He's a Bonobo."},{"time":151000,"text":"Right now, he's in a forest in Georgia."},{"time":154000,"text":"His mother originally came from a forest in Africa."},{"time":158000,"text":"And she came to us when she was just at puberty,"},{"time":162000,"text":"about six or seven years of age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165000,"text":"Now this shows a Bonobo on your right,"},{"time":167000,"text":"and a chimpanzee on your left."},{"time":169000,"text":"Clearly, the chimpanzee has a little bit harder time of walking."},{"time":173000,"text":"The Bonobo, although shorter than us and their arms still longer,"},{"time":177000,"text":"is more upright, just as we are."},{"time":181000,"text":"This shows the Bonobo compared to an australopithecine like Lucy."},{"time":186000,"text":"As you can see, there's not a lot of difference"},{"time":189000,"text":"between the way a Bonobo walks"},{"time":191000,"text":"and the way an early australopithecine would have walked."},{"time":195000,"text":"As they turn toward us you'll see"},{"time":197000,"text":"that the pelvic area of early australopithecines is a little flatter"},{"time":202000,"text":"and doesn't have to rotate quite so much from side to side."},{"time":206000,"text":"So the -- the bipedal gait is a little easier."},{"time":208000,"text":"And now we see all four."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211000,"text":"Video: Narrator: The wild Bonobo lives in central Africa, in the jungle"},{"time":215000,"text":"encircled by the Congo River."},{"time":220000,"text":"Canopied trees as tall as 40 meters, 130 feet,"},{"time":224000,"text":"grow densely in the area."},{"time":228000,"text":"It was a Japanese scientist"},{"time":231000,"text":"who first undertook serious field studies of the Bonobo,"},{"time":235000,"text":"almost three decades ago."},{"time":241000,"text":"Bonobos are built slightly smaller than the chimpanzee."},{"time":245000,"text":"Slim-bodied, Bonobos are by nature very gentle creatures."},{"time":251000,"text":"Long and careful studies have reported many new findings on them."},{"time":258000,"text":"One discovery was that wild Bonobos often walk bidpedally."},{"time":270000,"text":"What's more, they are able to walk upright for long distances."},{"time":282000,"text":"Susan Savage-Rumbaugh (video): Let's go say hello to Austin first and then go to the A frame."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286000,"text":"SS: This is Kanzi and I, in the forest."},{"time":288000,"text":"None of the things you will see in this particular video are trained."},{"time":292000,"text":"None of them are tricks."},{"time":294000,"text":"They all happened to be captured on film spontaneously,"},{"time":297000,"text":"by NHK of Japan."},{"time":300000,"text":"We have eight Bonobos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"Video: Look at all this stuff that's here for our campfire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"SS: An entire family at our research centre."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313000,"text":"Video: You going to help get some sticks?"},{"time":317000,"text":"Good."},{"time":322000,"text":"We need more sticks, too."},{"time":331000,"text":"I have a lighter in my pocket if you need one."},{"time":334000,"text":"That's a wasps' nest."},{"time":336000,"text":"You can get it out."},{"time":340000,"text":"I hope I have a lighter."},{"time":343000,"text":"You can use the lighter to start the fire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347000,"text":"SS: So Kanzi is very interested in fire."},{"time":349000,"text":"He doesn't do it yet without a lighter,"},{"time":352000,"text":"but I think if he saw someone do it, he might be able to do --"},{"time":356000,"text":"make a fire without a lighter."},{"time":360000,"text":"He's learning about how to keep a fire going."},{"time":363000,"text":"He's learning the uses for a fire,"},{"time":366000,"text":"just by watching what we do with fire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":378000,"text":"This is a smile on the face of a Bonobo."},{"time":380000,"text":"These are happy vocalizations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"Video: You're happy."},{"time":384000,"text":"You're very happy about this part."},{"time":386000,"text":"You've got to put some water on the fire. You see the water?"},{"time":395000,"text":"Good job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398000,"text":"SS: Forgot to zip up the back half of his backpack."},{"time":402000,"text":"But he likes to carry things from place to place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405000,"text":"Video: Austin, I hear you saying \"Austin.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":407000,"text":"SS: He talks to other Bonobos at the lab, long-distance,"},{"time":410000,"text":"farther than we can hear."},{"time":413000,"text":"This is his sister."},{"time":415000,"text":"This is her first time to try to drive a golf cart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420000,"text":"Video: Goodbye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"SS: She's got the pedals down, but not the wheel."},{"time":432000,"text":"She switches from reverse to forward"},{"time":435000,"text":"and she holds onto the wheel, rather than turns it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":440000,"text":"Like us, she knows that that individual in the mirror is her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"Video: Narrator: By raising Bonobos in a culture that is both Bonobo and human,"},{"time":454000,"text":"and documenting their development across two decades,"},{"time":458000,"text":"scientists are exploring how cultural forces"}]},{"cues":[{"time":461000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":462000,"text":"may have operated during human evolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"His name is Nyota."},{"time":469000,"text":"It means \"star\" in Swahili."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":481000,"text":"Panbanisha is trying to give Nyota a haircut with a pair of scissors."},{"time":487000,"text":"In the wild, the parent Bonobo is known to groom its offspring."},{"time":492000,"text":"Here Panbanisha uses scissors, instead of her hands,"},{"time":496000,"text":"to groom Nyota."},{"time":500000,"text":"Very impressive."},{"time":506000,"text":"Subtle maneuvering of the hands is required"},{"time":509000,"text":"to perform delicate tasks like this."},{"time":521000,"text":"Nyota tries to imitate Panbanisha by using the scissors himself."},{"time":528000,"text":"Realizing that Nyota might get hurt,"},{"time":531000,"text":"Panbanisha, like any human mother,"},{"time":533000,"text":"carefully tugs to get the scissors back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552000,"text":"He can now cut through tough animal hide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556000,"text":"SS: Kanzi's learned to make stone tools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558000,"text":"Video: Kanzi now makes his tools,"},{"time":559000,"text":"just as our ancestors may have made them,"},{"time":561000,"text":"two-and-a-half million years ago --"},{"time":563000,"text":"by holding the rocks in both hands, to strike one against the other."},{"time":568000,"text":"He has learned that by using both hands"},{"time":571000,"text":"and aiming his glancing blows,"},{"time":573000,"text":"he can make much larger, sharper flakes."},{"time":577000,"text":"Kanzi chooses a flake he thinks is sharp enough."},{"time":585000,"text":"The tough hide is difficult to cut, even with a knife."},{"time":589000,"text":"The rock that Kanzi is using is extremely hard"},{"time":592000,"text":"and ideal for stone tool making, but difficult to handle,"},{"time":596000,"text":"requiring great skill."},{"time":598000,"text":"Kanzi's rock is from Gona, Ethiopia"},{"time":600000,"text":"and is identical to that used by our African ancestors"},{"time":604000,"text":"two-and-a-half million years ago."},{"time":609000,"text":"These are the rocks Kanzi used"},{"time":612000,"text":"and these are the flakes he made."},{"time":614000,"text":"The flat sharp edges are like knife blades."},{"time":619000,"text":"Compare them to the tools our ancestors used;"},{"time":622000,"text":"they bear a striking resemblance to Kanzi's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635000,"text":"Panbanisha is longing to go for a walk in the woods."},{"time":638000,"text":"She keeps staring out the window."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643000,"text":"SS: This is -- let me show you something we didn't think they would do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646000,"text":"Video: For several days now, Panbanisha has not been outside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652000,"text":"SS: I normally talk about language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654000,"text":"Video: Then Panbanisha does something unexpected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657000,"text":"SS: But since I'm advised not to do what I normally do,"},{"time":660000,"text":"I haven't told you that these apes have language."},{"time":662000,"text":"It's a geometric language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"Video: She takes a piece of chalk"},{"time":665000,"text":"and begins writing something on the floor."},{"time":667000,"text":"What is she writing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":675000,"text":"SS: She's also saying the name of that, with her voice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679000,"text":"Video: Now she comes up to Dr. Sue and starts writing again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682000,"text":"SS: These are her symbols on her keyboard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":686000,"text":"They speak when she touches them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688000,"text":"Video: Panbanisha is communicating to Dr. Sue where she wants to go."},{"time":691000,"text":"\"A frame\" represents a hut in the woods."},{"time":695000,"text":"Compare the chalk writing with the lexigram on the keyboard."},{"time":709000,"text":"Panbanisha began writing the lexigrams on the forest floor."},{"time":715000,"text":"SS (video): Very nice. Beautiful, Panbanisha."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719000,"text":"SS: At first we didn't really realize what she was doing,"},{"time":722000,"text":"until we stood back and looked at it and rotated it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"Video: This lexigram also refers to a place in the woods."},{"time":727000,"text":"The curved line is very similar to the lexigram."},{"time":734000,"text":"The next symbol Panbanisha writes represents \"collar.\""},{"time":738000,"text":"It indicates the collar that Panbanisha must wear when she goes out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742000,"text":"SS: That's an institutional requirement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745000,"text":"Video: This symbol is not as clear as the others,"},{"time":748000,"text":"but one can see Panbanisha is trying to produce a curved line"},{"time":753000,"text":"and several straight lines."},{"time":755000,"text":"Researchers began to record what Panbanisha said,"},{"time":759000,"text":"by writing lexigrams on the floor with chalk."},{"time":763000,"text":"Panbanisha watched."},{"time":765000,"text":"Soon she began to write as well."},{"time":769000,"text":"The Bonobo's abilities have stunned scientists around the world."},{"time":773000,"text":"How did they develop?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"SS (video): We found that the most important thing"},{"time":777000,"text":"for permitting Bonobos to acquire language is not to teach them."},{"time":782000,"text":"It's simply to use language around them,"},{"time":785000,"text":"because the driving force in language acquisition"},{"time":788000,"text":"is to understand what others, that are important to you, are saying to you."},{"time":793000,"text":"Once you have that capacity,"},{"time":795000,"text":"the ability to produce language"},{"time":798000,"text":"comes rather naturally and rather freely."},{"time":802000,"text":"So we want to create an environment in which Bonobos,"},{"time":805000,"text":"like all of the individuals with whom they are interacting --"},{"time":809000,"text":"we want to create an environment in which they have fun,"},{"time":812000,"text":"and an environment in which the others"},{"time":814000,"text":"are meaningful individuals for them."},{"time":819000,"text":"Narrator: This environment brings out unexpected potential"},{"time":822000,"text":"in Kanzi and Panbanisha."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832000,"text":"Panbanisha is enjoying playing her harmonica,"},{"time":836000,"text":"until Nyota, now one year old, steals it."},{"time":840000,"text":"Then he peers eagerly into his mother's mouth."},{"time":844000,"text":"Is he looking for where the sound came from?"},{"time":847000,"text":"Dr. Sue thinks it's important to allow such curiosity to flourish."},{"time":862000,"text":"This time Panbanisha is playing the electric piano."},{"time":865000,"text":"She wasn't forced to learn the piano;"},{"time":868000,"text":"she saw a researcher play the instrument and took an interest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900000,"text":"Researcher: Go ahead. Go ahead. I'm listening."},{"time":904000,"text":"Do that real fast part that you did. Yeah, that part."}]},{"cues":[{"time":911000,"text":"Narrator: Kanzi plays the xylophone;"},{"time":913000,"text":"using both hands he enthusiastically accompanies Dr. Sue's singing."},{"time":919000,"text":"Kanzi and Panbanisha"},{"time":920000,"text":"are stimulated by this fun-filled environment,"},{"time":923000,"text":"which promotes the emergence of these cultural capabilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":941000,"text":"Researcher: OK, now get the monsters. Get them."},{"time":944000,"text":"Take the cherries too."},{"time":947000,"text":"Now watch out, stay away from them now."},{"time":951000,"text":"Now you can chase them again. Time to chase them."},{"time":958000,"text":"Now you have to stay away. Get away."},{"time":961000,"text":"Run away. Run."},{"time":964000,"text":"Now we can chase them again. Go get them."},{"time":970000,"text":"Oh no!"},{"time":972000,"text":"Good Kanzi. Very good. Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":979000,"text":"Narrator: None of us, Bonobo or human, can possibly even imagine?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":992000,"text":"SS: So we have a bi-species environment, we call it a \"panhomoculture.\""},{"time":999000,"text":"We're learning how to become like them."},{"time":1001000,"text":"We're learning how to communicate with them,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"in really high-pitched tones."},{"time":1005000,"text":"We're learning that they probably have a language in the wild."},{"time":1009000,"text":"And they're learning to become like us."},{"time":1011000,"text":"Because we believe that it's not biology; it's culture."},{"time":1014000,"text":"So we're sharing tools and technology and language"},{"time":1018000,"text":"with another species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1020000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}